      "content": "Relying on skipping doses every time you have a light dinner is a shortcut that can lead to long-term issues. While it feels easier now, it teaches your body to expect less insulin, which can cause spikes later on. Instead, try a small, easily digestible snack before bed—like a few almonds or a piece of fruit—to give your body something to work with. This small addition is far more consistent than guessing when to skip your medication.",
